  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Serial quantitative measurements of plasma pro-endothelin-1 concentrations in very preterm
      infants. Comparing pro-endothelin-1 with established clinical indices of bronchopulmonary
      dysplasia (BPD). Hypothesis: Pulmonary-vascular remodeling in infants developing BPD is
      directly related to circulating pro-endothelin-1, which therefore serves as surrogate marker
      of BPD.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
